    "body": "The ctb_prompt was needed because of how the prompt area is sized.  It has a width in ex units, but a padding in em.  The padding in em is needed to match what CodeMirror uses and the ex units are the right units to use to get the prompt area to shrink/grow as the font size changes.  The other complication is that browsers change the pixel meaning of ex and em based on the font size.  This is what was causing the misalignment when changing the font size on Linux.  The only clean way of fixing this is to put the ctb_prompt div there and have it sized in exactly the same way as the real prompt area.\n"
  },
